Now if we make a true colour
image of a galaxy,

239
00:12:52,916 --> 00:12:55,856
with this spectral distribution,

240
00:12:55,856 --> 00:12:57,997
we will have typically, a galaxy,

241
00:12:57,997 --> 00:12:59,627
as we can see here,

